The global vacation rental market has been witnessing significant growth in recent years driven by factors such as increasing consumer preference for personalized and unique travel experiences, growing popularity of online booking platforms, and the rise of the sharing economy. With the rising trend of experiential travel, more travelers are opting for vacation rentals over traditional hotels to enjoy a home-like environment and local cultural experiences during their trips. Additionally, the flexibility, cost-effectiveness, and larger accommodation options offered by vacation rentals have further fueled the market growth.

